00:38:16,574 --> 00:38:20,374
- You got a big mouth, you know that?
- Hey, you're that new kid...

665
00:38:20,445 --> 00:38:23,312
The one that everyone says
is the best baseball player in town.

666
00:38:23,381 --> 00:38:26,282
No, no, no. I'm the new kid
that's asking you politely...

667
00:38:26,351 --> 00:38:28,376
to let the kid go on his way.

668
00:38:28,453 --> 00:38:31,149
- And if we don't?
- Do you really wanna find out?

669
00:38:31,222 --> 00:38:33,486
You're outnumbered seven to one.

670
00:38:33,558 --> 00:38:36,026
Yeah, and the odds
aren't exactly in your favor.

671
00:38:39,564 --> 00:38:42,692
<i>[D.P.]</i>
<i>Everything cool over here?</i>

672
00:38:42,767 --> 00:38:45,998
[Whistles]
Saved by the cavalry.

673
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:49,369
I don't need them to take you on, E.J.

674
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:52,307
You'll need anything
you can get your hands on...

675
00:38:52,377 --> 00:38:54,572
- "Santa-smelly."
- Okay, look.

676
00:38:54,646 --> 00:38:59,049
I'm not gonna get into this sophomoric,
name-calling contest with a kid.

677
00:38:59,117 --> 00:39:01,415
Frankly, it's beneath me.

678
00:39:01,486 --> 00:39:04,478
Well, maybe it's because
you're a "lame-oid" loser...

679
00:39:04,555 --> 00:39:06,887
- with pimple breath.
- That's an intelligent comeback.

680
00:39:06,958 --> 00:39:11,986
Got any more, Einstein?
Or is that all your pea brain is capable of?

681
00:39:12,063 --> 00:39:15,260
- [Laughter]
- "Pea brain"? That's a really good one, man.

682
00:39:15,333 --> 00:39:17,494
You gonna let him
get away with that, E. J?

683
00:39:17,568 --> 00:39:19,559
You know, you should
spend more time...

684
00:39:19,637 --> 00:39:21,662
working on your baseball practice
than your weak insults.

685
00:39:21,739 --> 00:39:24,264
- Insulting you isn't work.
- Oh, yeah?

686
00:39:24,342 --> 00:39:27,004
It comes pretty easy.

687
00:39:27,078 --> 00:39:30,741
Dog face. Turd mouth.
Rotten-faced bonehead.

688
00:39:30,815 --> 00:39:33,841
Ignorant, pathetic
sociopath-in-training.

689
00:39:33,918 --> 00:39:37,445
I have no idea what that means,
but it sounded good, guys.

690
00:39:37,522 --> 00:39:38,955
- Yeah.
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

691
00:39:39,023 --> 00:39:41,548
At least my girlfriend
doesn't wear a collar.

692
00:39:41,626 --> 00:39:43,958
I heard your girlfriend got
kicked out of an ugly contest...

693
00:39:44,028 --> 00:39:46,622
because they said
no professionals allowed.

694
00:39:46,698 --> 00:39:48,859
[Laughing]

695
00:39:48,933 --> 00:39:54,530
Now, is it true that your mother
smacked the doctor when you were born?

696
00:39:54,605 --> 00:39:57,403
- [Imitates Rim Shot]
- Oh. Speaking of mothers...

697
00:39:57,475 --> 00:40:00,035
do you guys need another player?

698
00:40:00,111 --> 00:40:03,103
'Cause my mom plays ball pretty good,
and she's better than all you fools.

699
00:40:03,181 --> 00:40:05,877
[Chattering]

700
00:40:07,452 --> 00:40:09,977
Sorry. What was that?
Go ahead.

701
00:40:10,054 --> 00:40:13,421
Go ahead. Go ahead. I can't...
I can't hear you. I'm listening. Go ahead.

702
00:40:14,525 --> 00:40:17,653
Well, at least my mom's not sick.

703
00:40:25,369 --> 00:40:30,272
You ever say something
like that again, I will ruin you.

704
00:40:30,341 --> 00:40:34,437
- Oh, yeah?
- Don't mess with me on this, E.J.

705
00:40:34,512 --> 00:40:37,447
I'll go Tarantino on you so fast...

706
00:40:37,515 --> 00:40:40,780
- <i>you won't know what hit you.</i>
- Tear a what?

707
00:40:40,852 --> 00:40:42,911
That's some kind of martial arts.

708
00:40:42,987 --> 00:40:44,978
In moron terms...

709
00:40:45,056 --> 00:40:47,149
it means I'm gonna hurt you.

710
00:40:47,225 --> 00:40:51,662
I'm gonna hurt you real bad,
you got that?

711
00:41:05,276 --> 00:41:08,507
And you, weirdo.
Next time be a man.

712
00:41:08,579 --> 00:41:11,377
Fight your own battles.
Let's go, guys.

713
00:41:12,517 --> 00:41:14,542
Yeah, beat it.

714
00:41:14,619 --> 00:41:17,611
- Get out of here.
- We don't like you here anyway.

715
00:41:17,688 --> 00:41:20,714
You okay, man?

716
00:41:20,792 --> 00:41:23,989
- Do we get to play him?
- [All] Yeah.

717
00:41:24,061 --> 00:41:26,325
<i>Sure do.</i>

718
00:41:30,735 --> 00:41:33,670
- I'm in.
- [All] Yeah!

719
00:41:33,738 --> 00:41:36,639
<i>[Cheering]</i>

720
00:41:36,707 --> 00:41:38,732
Hey, Mom, I was thinking
about joining a team...

721
00:41:38,810 --> 00:41:40,869
with those kids from the movie
the other night.

722
00:41:40,945 --> 00:41:43,880
That's if you're feeling okay.
Are you down with that?

723
00:41:43,948 --> 00:41:45,973
Honey, I'm feeling fine.

724
00:41:46,050 --> 00:41:48,814
And why would you possibly think
I'd be down with it?

725
00:41:48,886 --> 00:41:51,684
I'm definitely up with it.

726
00:41:51,756 --> 00:41:53,917
Cool.

727
00:41:53,991 --> 00:41:56,050
- <i>[Door Opens, Closes]</i>
- Groovy.

728
00:41:56,260 --> 00:41:58,228
- If you want it to ride?
- Mm-hmm?

729
00:41:58,296 --> 00:42:00,321
- Throw it two-seam, okay?
- Two seam?

730
00:42:00,398 --> 00:42:02,593
Come on, Timber, let's go.

731
00:42:02,667 --> 00:42:05,227
- Two seam.
- Right down the middle.

732
00:42:07,605 --> 00:42:11,041
Ow! Timber, take it easy.

733
00:42:11,108 --> 00:42:13,406
Come on, D.P. You're such a wimp.
Get in the game.

734
00:42:13,477 --> 00:42:17,038
What are you whining about?
Why don't you come and play catcher.

735
00:42:17,114 --> 00:42:21,551
- That's where you belong anyhow.
- Just because I'm husky doesn't mean
I have to play catcher.

736
00:42:21,619 --> 00:42:22,745
- Two Ton?
- <i>What?</i>

737
00:42:22,820 --> 00:42:24,720
- You're not husky.
- See?

738
00:42:24,789 --> 00:42:26,916
- You're fat.
- <i>That's it.</i>

739
00:42:26,991 --> 00:42:30,222
The death of Wok and Roll,
right here, right now. Come here!

740
00:42:30,294 --> 00:42:32,888
- Whoa!
- <i>Run!</i>
- Guys!

741
00:42:32,964 --> 00:42:35,956
Can we play some baseball?

742
00:42:36,033 --> 00:42:37,967
- Is practice always like this?
- <i>No.</i>

743
00:42:38,035 --> 00:42:40,799
- Sometimes Two Ton chases somebody else.
- <i>Come on, Timber.</i>

744
00:42:40,872 --> 00:42:43,432
- Just pretend like I'm not here, okay?
- Batter up, guys. Let's go.

745
00:42:43,507 --> 00:42:45,702
- Two seam again?
- Two seam.

746
00:42:45,776 --> 00:42:48,904
Just try to hit my bat, okay?

747
00:42:48,980 --> 00:42:53,246
- [Groans]
- Ooh! Sorry.

748
00:42:53,317 --> 00:42:55,581
Gee!
[Groans]

749
00:42:55,653 --> 00:42:57,917
Wrong bat, Timber.

750
00:42:57,989 --> 00:43:00,617
- Guys, look at this.
- [Groaning Continues]

751
00:43:00,691 --> 00:43:03,455
What are we gonna do
about Timber's control problems?

752
00:43:05,529 --> 00:43:07,827
<i>I bet Wings has got</i>
<i>some good ideas.</i>

753
00:43:07,899 --> 00:43:12,063
[High Voice]
Timber, if I live, you're dead.

754
00:43:12,136 --> 00:43:14,661
I don't know about you guys,
but I'm gettin' a cup.

755
00:43:16,674 --> 00:43:19,404
- Hey, Two Ton.
- What do you want?

756
00:43:19,477 --> 00:43:21,604
I got a hurts doughnut.
You want one?

757
00:43:21,679 --> 00:43:24,113
- Doughnut? Sure.
- Okay.

758
00:43:24,181 --> 00:43:26,411
Ow!

759
00:43:26,484 --> 00:43:29,248
- Hurts, don't it?
- Hurts, don't it?

760
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:31,914
You know something?
You guys are better than I remember.

761
00:43:31,989 --> 00:43:34,787
With a little help from me,
I can hammer you into a winning team.

762
00:43:34,859 --> 00:43:38,317
<i>How ever can we repay you,</i>
<i>your holiness of baseball?</i>

763
00:43:38,396 --> 00:43:41,854
Look. All we wanted you to do
was play with us 'cause you're real good.

764
00:43:41,933 --> 00:43:44,265
We didn't ask you
to coach or anything.

765
00:43:44,335 --> 00:43:47,099
Squints coaches the games,
and Benny comes by when he can.

766
00:43:47,171 --> 00:43:50,265
- We just needed another player.
- How often can Benny come by?

767
00:43:50,341 --> 00:43:52,172
His team's hanging on by a thread...

768
00:43:52,243 --> 00:43:54,677
and with me gone,
he's got nobody to work with.

769
00:43:58,582 --> 00:44:00,311
What you talkin' about?

770
00:44:00,384 --> 00:44:04,150
I heard Benny the Jet hurt his knee
in Cincinnati last night.

771
00:44:04,221 --> 00:44:08,624
I heard it's pretty serious. Uncle Chops
said he was gonna be out for six weeks.

772
00:44:08,693 --> 00:44:12,629
Hey, knowing Benny, he'll be playing in two.
That knee's always trouble.

773
00:44:12,697 --> 00:44:16,497
Yeah? In '96, he got that replaced
and it ended his car...

774
00:44:16,567 --> 00:44:19,900
- Car... Career?
- <i>1996?</i>

775
00:44:19,971 --> 00:44:22,804
- I've gotta go.
<i>- [D.P.] Replaced his knee?</i>

776
00:44:22,873 --> 00:44:26,639
But if we are gonna be a real team,
we're gonna need some equipment...

777
00:44:26,711 --> 00:44:30,044
bats, balls, a new glove for Wings
and some pads for D.P.

778
00:44:30,114 --> 00:44:32,048
<i>The last thing I wanna be is a coach.</i>

779
00:44:32,116 --> 00:44:34,346
I just figure
that if we're gonna play...

780
00:44:34,418 --> 00:44:37,683
we should play like pros
and play to win.

781
00:44:37,755 --> 00:44:39,814
See ya.

782
00:44:41,158 --> 00:44:43,183
<i>[Indistinct Conversations]</i>

783
00:44:43,260 --> 00:44:46,696
- Order!
- [Chattering]

784
00:44:46,764 --> 00:44:49,892
<i>Please, people.</i>

785
00:44:49,967 --> 00:44:53,733
- Mr. Needman still has the floor.
- Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

786
00:44:53,804 --> 00:44:58,104
I know most of you have a sentimental
attachment to that old sandlot.

787
00:44:58,175 --> 00:45:01,736
Heck, I even used to play ball
there myself, back in the day.

788
00:45:01,812 --> 00:45:04,542
<i>The truth of the matter is...</i>

789
00:45:04,615 --> 00:45:08,676
that old sandlot is sitting
smack-dab in the middle...

790
00:45:08,753 --> 00:45:11,620
of some very profitable land
for this town.

791
00:45:11,689 --> 00:45:16,854
<i>Now, I am not gonna stand up here</i>
<i>and lie to you fine people...</i>

792
00:45:16,927 --> 00:45:19,395
and tell you that
I'm not in this to make a buck...

793
00:45:19,463 --> 00:45:21,454
because I am,
and I sure will.

794
00:45:21,532 --> 00:45:25,730
<i>The fact remains, this town</i>
<i>has seen some hard times lately...</i>

795
00:45:25,803 --> 00:45:28,931
and we could use this.

796
00:45:29,006 --> 00:45:32,271
Now if this council votes
to allow me to build...

797
00:45:32,343 --> 00:45:36,439
<i>the condominiums I'm proposing</i>
<i>will bring nice, affordable housing...</i>

798
00:45:36,514 --> 00:45:39,540
more jobs and more pride.

799
00:45:39,617 --> 00:45:42,609
Now let's be honest.
Who couldn't use a little of that nowadays?

800
00:45:42,686 --> 00:45:45,154
I can't believe this.
Come on, folks.

801
00:45:45,222 --> 00:45:48,157
The only thing that Earl Needman
has ever cared about...

802
00:45:48,225 --> 00:45:51,956
- <i>is fattening his wallet.</i>
- <i>[Man] That's right.</i>

803
00:45:52,029 --> 00:45:54,827
Now, if we vote
to let him do this now...

804
00:45:54,899 --> 00:45:57,493
we're losing something more important
than any of us can imagine.

805
00:45:57,568 --> 00:46:00,059
And what would that,
Mr. Palledorous?

806
00:46:00,137 --> 00:46:02,799
- Our history.
- <i>[Man] Yeah.</i>

807
00:46:02,873 --> 00:46:07,276
And our future. How many of you
grew up playing ball in that field?

808
00:46:07,344 --> 00:46:10,142
- <i>[Man] I did.</i>
- <i>And how many of you...</i>

809
00:46:10,214 --> 00:46:13,775
are willing to take that
opportunity away from your kids?

810
00:46:13,851 --> 00:46:18,311
This man is,
unless we stop him now.

811
00:46:18,389 --> 00:46:21,688
[Cheering, Chattering]

812
00:46:31,068 --> 00:46:35,630
Well, it, uh, seems
we all have a lot to consider.

813
00:46:35,706 --> 00:46:38,470
We'll reconvene next
on July the second...

814
00:46:38,542 --> 00:46:41,670
and we'll decide
on this matter then, huh?

815
00:46:41,745 --> 00:46:45,772
- Meeting adjourned.
- [Chattering]

816
00:46:45,850 --> 00:46:49,342
People, this is the chance
of a lifetime.

817
00:46:49,420 --> 00:46:52,787
<i>Chance of a lifetime! People...</i>

818
00:46:53,023 --> 00:46:56,652
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

819
00:46:56,727 --> 00:46:59,389
<i>[Echoing]</i>
<i>Chance of a lifetime...</i>

820
00:47:01,565 --> 00:47:04,466
[Echoing]
Tommy.

821
00:47:04,535 --> 00:47:07,060
Wake up, darling.

822
00:47:07,138 --> 00:47:10,665
- [Groans] What happened?
- <i>You crashed after the game.</i>

823
00:47:10,741 --> 00:47:13,642
You've been asleep for a few hours now,
but Lou's here to see you.

824
00:47:13,711 --> 00:47:15,702
- Lou? What's my agent doing here?
- [Cell Phone Ringing]

825
00:47:15,779 --> 00:47:18,680
That's me. Lou.

826
00:47:18,749 --> 00:47:20,979
That's chump change.
Call me back with the real deal.

827
00:47:21,051 --> 00:47:23,178
I've got shoes
that cost more than that.

828
00:47:23,254 --> 00:47:26,917
<i>New York Yankees.</i>
<i>The Big Apple, baby!</i>

829
00:47:26,991 --> 00:47:30,893
<i>New York? But, Tommy,</i>
<i>I took my residency here.</i>

830
00:47:30,961 --> 00:47:33,987
Babe, we're talking
about the New York Yankees.

831
00:47:34,064 --> 00:47:36,259
That's 3,000 miles away.

832
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:39,268
Tommy is a money machine.
The owners, they want to buy him, okay?

833
00:47:39,336 --> 00:47:41,361
The fans, they want to pay to see him.

834
00:47:41,438 --> 00:47:43,429
He is what baseball should be...

835
00:47:43,507 --> 00:47:46,499
caps, T-shirts, memorabilia,
cash just for signing your name.

836
00:47:46,577 --> 00:47:49,045
They have these things called
bobble-head dolls now. All right?

837
00:47:49,113 --> 00:47:52,378
It's payday,
and New York is the ticket.

838
00:47:52,449 --> 00:47:55,111
That's the way it was,
the way it always will be.

839
00:47:55,186 --> 00:47:58,087
Yankees! Yankees.

840
00:47:58,155 --> 00:48:00,851
They are making me
the offer of a lifetime.

841
00:48:00,925 --> 00:48:03,553
- I thought that's what I was doing.
- <i>[Tapping]</i>

842
00:48:03,627 --> 00:48:05,788
- Can you hear that?
- Not now.

843
00:48:05,863 --> 00:48:09,856
Tommy, this is us we're talking about.
Baby, I love you.

844
00:48:09,934 --> 00:48:11,925
Judy, no!
[Panting]

845
00:48:12,002 --> 00:48:14,835
<i>[Judy's Voice]</i>
<i>You're not gonna get another chance.</i>

846
00:48:18,342 --> 00:48:21,641
- <i>[Tapping]</i>
- <i>[D.P.] Tommy, wake up.</i>

847
00:48:21,712 --> 00:48:25,773
<i>Tommy, you're gonna miss</i>
<i>the chance of a lifetime.</i>

848
00:48:25,849 --> 00:48:28,716
Come on. Open it.

849
00:48:28,786 --> 00:48:32,483
We're going to get
that equipment you talked about.

850
00:48:32,556 --> 00:48:35,616
- In the middle of the night? What's open?
- Old Man Mertle's house.

851
00:48:35,693 --> 00:48:38,560
- [Q] Yeah.
- It sounds like breaking and entering.

852
00:48:38,629 --> 00:48:41,097
- The place is abandoned.
- Except for the treasure.

853
00:48:41,165 --> 00:48:42,996
You want to stay
on the right side of the law.

854
00:48:43,067 --> 00:48:47,731
- [Imitating Chickens]
- Told you he wouldn't go.

855
00:48:47,805 --> 00:48:50,330
Come on. Let pretty boy here
get his beauty sleep.

856
00:48:50,407 --> 00:48:53,240
Go now, Tommy. You're not gonna
get a second chance at this.

857
00:48:55,079 --> 00:48:56,944
Hold on. I'll come.

858
00:48:57,147 --> 00:48:59,615
- <i>[Thunder]</i>
- <i>[Two Ton] Can somebody please tell me...</i>

859
00:48:59,683 --> 00:49:01,742
<i>why we didn't go over the back fence?</i>

860
00:49:01,819 --> 00:49:05,812
<i>[Wok] Because pushing your fat butt</i>
<i>over could get real stinky.</i>

861
00:49:05,889 --> 00:49:09,416
[D.P.] So I heard that Mr. Mertle
was once a great baseball player...

862
00:49:09,493 --> 00:49:12,462
until he went blind after getting hit
with a baseball in the head.

863
00:49:12,529 --> 00:49:15,464
Legend has it that he has a secret stash
of old baseball stuff.

864
00:49:15,532 --> 00:49:17,659
[Tommy]
So what ever happened to Mr. Mertle?

865
00:49:17,735 --> 00:49:21,466
Some say he just died.
Others say he up and vanished.

866
00:49:21,538 --> 00:49:24,939
- Hit in the head with a baseball?
- Vanished?

867
00:49:25,009 --> 00:49:27,637
<i>[Thunder]</i>

868
00:49:30,414 --> 00:49:34,680
- <i>[Two Ton] Guys, I just saw something move.</i>
- <i>Guys, it's just a house.</i>

869
00:49:34,752 --> 00:49:37,516
- If we're going to do this, let's do it.
- <i>What about the ghost?</i>

870
00:49:37,588 --> 00:49:42,890
[D.P.] All right. Come on. Let's go.
All right. Move! Move! Move!

871
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:45,827
- [All] Shut up, D. P!
- All right, move your butts.

872
00:49:45,896 --> 00:49:49,696
- <i>[Wok] Hey, check it out.</i>
- <i>[Roll] Hercules?</i>
<i>Who names their dog Hercules?</i>

873
00:49:49,767 --> 00:49:51,962
It was probably just some
Chihuahua or something.

874
00:49:52,036 --> 00:49:55,005
You know how people name their dog
just the opposite of what they are.

875
00:49:55,072 --> 00:49:58,007
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

876
00:49:58,075 --> 00:50:01,306
- That must have been a <i>grande</i> Chihuahua, man.
- % % [Whistles]

877
00:50:01,378 --> 00:50:04,142
- <i>[Thunder]</i>
- [Boy] Let's go.

878
00:50:08,986 --> 00:50:12,820
<i>This... This is crazy, guys.</i>
<i>That's it. I'm out of here.</i>

879
00:50:12,890 --> 00:50:17,486
<i>Oh, come on. Don't be such a wuss.</i>
<i>I thought we were a team.</i>

880
00:50:17,561 --> 00:50:19,825
All right, then.
Go ahead, you're up.

881
00:50:19,897 --> 00:50:25,199
I say we send in one of the little guys,
kind of like a scout.

882
00:50:25,269 --> 00:50:27,829
Since when does the shortest guy
have to go first?

883
00:50:27,905 --> 00:50:30,339
When the taller guys tell him to.

884
00:50:30,407 --> 00:50:33,433
- <i>Speaking of short guys, where's Ryan?</i>
- <i>[Wok] Yeah, where is he?</i>

885
00:50:33,510 --> 00:50:37,344
- <i>Where is he? He was here?</i>
- [All Screaming]

886
00:50:37,414 --> 00:50:41,407
<i>[Barking]</i>

887
00:50:42,653 --> 00:50:46,020
- It's Ryan!
- Ohh!

888
00:50:46,090 --> 00:50:49,582
- Gutsy move, kid. Pretty impressive.
- <i>[Boy] What was that for?</i>

889
00:50:49,660 --> 00:50:53,653
<i>[Tommy] You guys check this floor.</i>
<i>I'll check upstairs.</i>

890
00:51:04,308 --> 00:51:07,175
[All Screaming]

891
00:51:11,215 --> 00:51:13,308
[Exhales]

892
00:51:22,693 --> 00:51:25,890
That's a big baseball.

893
00:51:25,963 --> 00:51:28,727
- [Shouting]
- [Screaming]

894
00:51:28,799 --> 00:51:31,233
That's not funny, you idiot!

895
00:51:31,301 --> 00:51:35,965
<i>Whoa! That's a big baseball.</i>

896
00:51:50,487 --> 00:51:52,751
<i>[Thunder]</i>

897
00:51:52,823 --> 00:51:54,950
[Both Scream]

898
00:51:55,025 --> 00:51:57,357
[Both Sigh]

899
00:51:57,428 --> 00:51:59,453
- You stay here.
- Yeah.

900
00:51:59,530 --> 00:52:02,499
- I'm gonna check over there, okay?
- Yeah.

901
00:52:10,607 --> 00:52:13,633
<i>[Squeaking]</i>

902
00:52:13,710 --> 00:52:15,701
- Bats!
- Baseball bats?

903
00:52:15,779 --> 00:52:19,180
- No, bat bats!
- <i>[Squeaking]</i>

904
00:52:19,249 --> 00:52:21,080
[Both Screaming]

905
00:52:22,352 --> 00:52:25,617
If I were something
really important...

906
00:52:25,689 --> 00:52:27,782
<i>where would I be?</i>

907
00:52:32,863 --> 00:52:36,355
- <i>[Sighs] Let's go, guys.</i>
- Come on.

908
00:52:36,433 --> 00:52:38,628
<i>[Thunder]</i>

909
00:52:39,703 --> 00:52:42,968
[Both Screaming]

910
00:52:43,040 --> 00:52:46,999
- There's nothing down there.
- <i>Except for bats.</i>

911
00:52:47,077 --> 00:52:51,207
- <i>[Timber] Baseball bats?</i>
- [Together] No. Bats bats.

912
00:52:51,281 --> 00:52:53,545
Oh, okay. There's nothing
here, either.

913
00:52:53,617 --> 00:52:56,814
Yeah, this place is a bust.
Hey, up there. Let's beat it.

914
00:52:56,887 --> 00:52:58,912
- <i>Come on, let's go.</i>
- Let's go.

915
00:52:58,989 --> 00:53:01,048
Come on, guys.

916
00:53:22,145 --> 00:53:24,170
What is that?

917
00:53:24,248 --> 00:53:27,706
<i>My best guess would be a hole.</i>

918
00:53:35,292 --> 00:53:37,954
Bingo.

919
00:53:52,175 --> 00:53:56,612
- I told you there's treasure in here.
- This is treasure, all right.

920
00:53:56,680 --> 00:54:00,081
But why leave it
in such an obvious place?

921
00:54:00,150 --> 00:54:03,278
<i>[Clunking, Creaking]</i>

922
00:54:07,858 --> 00:54:10,156
I've got a bad feeling
about this, guys.

923
00:54:10,227 --> 00:54:12,252
What should we do?

924
00:54:12,329 --> 00:54:15,059
[Together]
Run!

925
00:54:17,434 --> 00:54:19,425
Hey, guys!

926
00:54:19,503 --> 00:54:23,098
- <i>[Screaming]</i>
- <i>[All Screaming]</i>

927
00:54:23,173 --> 00:54:25,971
<i>% % [Man Singing]</i>

928
00:54:28,312 --> 00:54:31,076
- [Screaming]
- Get it off!

929
00:54:32,916 --> 00:54:36,613
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

930
00:54:38,522 --> 00:54:40,615
Oh, no.

931
00:55:37,314 --> 00:55:41,614
- <i>[Rumbling]</i>
- <i>% % [Continues]</i>

932
00:55:46,923 --> 00:55:50,518
[Screaming]

933
00:55:56,700 --> 00:56:00,295
That's a big baseball.

934
00:56:08,145 --> 00:56:10,238
- <i>% % [Ends]</i>
- [D.P.] You brought the ball?

935
00:56:10,313 --> 00:56:14,545
- Of course.
- Then I think we've got everything.

936
00:56:14,618 --> 00:56:18,213
- We do now. This is the real treasure.
- <i>[Two Ton] Whoa.</i>

937
00:56:18,288 --> 00:56:23,055
<i>[D.P.] Yeah, it's signed by all</i>
<i>the '63 Dodgers. Koufax. Drysdale.</i>

938
00:56:23,126 --> 00:56:26,425
- Tommy Davis.
- The whole team!

939
00:56:26,496 --> 00:56:29,727
- I say we sell it.
- That's loco.
- No, you loco.

940
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:32,530
- Imagine what you can get for this on eBay.
- [Together] What bay?

941
00:56:32,602 --> 00:56:38,063
Nothing. I don't ever think we should
sell this ball. I mean, it's why we found it.

942
00:56:38,141 --> 00:56:40,541
Old man Mertle's
trying to tell us something.

943
00:56:40,610 --> 00:56:44,068
- I think he's right, guys.
- So what do you say? Deal?

944
00:56:44,147 --> 00:56:46,479
- [All] Deal!
- Our ball!

945
00:56:46,550 --> 00:56:48,916
- Our lucky charm.
- Our championship.

946
00:56:48,985 --> 00:56:52,318
- On three, guys. One, two, three!
- [All] Sandlots!

947
00:56:52,389 --> 00:56:55,119
- Yeah!
- Let's go!

948
00:57:10,574 --> 00:57:13,236
Now, I've seen it
time and time again.

949
00:57:13,310 --> 00:57:15,710
Teams not playing
up to their full potential.

950
00:57:15,779 --> 00:57:18,009
- Time and time again?
- I've been around, Wings.

951
00:57:18,081 --> 00:57:20,982
<i>Now, listen, the thing of it is,</i>
<i>you guys could be good.</i>

952
00:57:21,051 --> 00:57:25,511
<i>You guys got the stuff, but we're going</i>
<i>to have to work on some basics...</i>

953
00:57:25,589 --> 00:57:29,525
play heads-up ball,
work together as a team, all right?

954
00:57:29,593 --> 00:57:31,857
- Yeah!
- All right.

955
00:57:31,928 --> 00:57:35,455
- Now just remember, baseball's more than just...
- Talent.

956
00:57:35,532 --> 00:57:37,796
- <i>Benny?</i>
- Benny!

957
00:57:37,868 --> 00:57:40,462
- <i>What's up, man?</i>
- <i>Hey!</i>

958
00:57:40,537 --> 00:57:42,767
- <i>Hey, man.</i>
- <i>Hey, how's it going? We missed you.</i>

959
00:57:42,839 --> 00:57:46,434
- <i>How's the ankle, man?</i>
- Oh, it's okay. I figured instead
of laying around the house...

960
00:57:46,510 --> 00:57:49,274
I'd come out and see how
the old sandlot gang is doing, right?

961
00:57:49,346 --> 00:57:52,315
- Yeah!
- What about you, Santorelli?

962
00:57:52,382 --> 00:57:55,180
Seems like you've had
a change of heart since a few days ago.

963
00:57:55,252 --> 00:57:57,812
I've seen some things, that's all.

964
00:57:57,888 --> 00:58:00,880
Yeah? Well, I'm glad.

965
00:58:00,957 --> 00:58:04,393
What do you say you take center field,
then shag some fly balls?

966
00:58:04,461 --> 00:58:09,694
I mean, that is, if there's room
for more than one coach on this team.

967
00:58:09,766 --> 00:58:14,328
- [Chuckles]
- I'd say that's... boffanado!

968
00:58:14,404 --> 00:58:16,531
[All]
Yeah!

969
00:58:16,606 --> 00:58:19,700
- <i>Here, let me take those for you.</i>
- Ah, thanks, D.P.

970
00:58:19,776 --> 00:58:22,040
Thanks, Benny.

971
00:58:22,112 --> 00:58:24,171
- Right here, Benny.
- Come on, Ben.

972
00:58:24,247 --> 00:58:26,238
All right, let's turn two!

973
00:58:26,316 --> 00:58:29,683
- <i>% % [Man Singing]</i>
- <i>Nice.</i>

974
00:58:29,753 --> 00:58:32,313
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

975
00:58:34,624 --> 00:58:38,651
Turn two.
Hit the cutoff.

976
00:58:52,843 --> 00:58:55,437
- Slide!
- There you go!

977
00:58:55,512 --> 00:59:00,677
- <i>% % [Continues]</i>
- Come on. Come on.

978
00:59:00,750 --> 00:59:02,377
All right!

979
00:59:09,693 --> 00:59:12,457
<i>[Benny]</i>
<i>Okay. New plan.</i>

980
00:59:23,006 --> 00:59:25,031
Okay, try it again.

981
00:59:26,610 --> 00:59:29,101
D.P., give me a target.

982
00:59:31,381 --> 00:59:33,042
Yes!

983
00:59:40,023 --> 00:59:42,150
Dig, dig, dig, dig, dig!

984
00:59:43,960 --> 00:59:45,655
All right, he was out.

985
00:59:45,729 --> 00:59:48,254
All right, so.
Ear, chin, ear, chin.

986
00:59:48,331 --> 00:59:50,799
<i>Slap, slap, slap.</i>

987
01:00:03,480 --> 01:00:06,916
<i>Good jobs, you guys.</i>
<i>All right, bring it in. Bring it in.</i>

988
01:00:06,983 --> 01:00:09,645
- <i>% % [Ends]</i>
- [Groans]

989
01:00:09,719 --> 01:00:11,778
- Nice catch.
- [Chattering]

990
01:00:11,855 --> 01:00:15,347
Yeah, that was...
that was so groovy.

991
01:00:15,425 --> 01:00:17,484
Well, what do you say, Santorelli?

992
01:00:17,560 --> 01:00:19,687
Think these guys are ready
for the city tournament?

993
01:00:19,763 --> 01:00:21,958
Yeah, I think they can bring it.

994
01:00:22,032 --> 01:00:24,159
- Bring it? What?
- <i>What?</i>

995
01:00:24,234 --> 01:00:27,829
- What were we supposed to bring?
- Home. Bring it home to the sandlot!

996
01:00:27,904 --> 01:00:31,305
- [All] Oh!
- Not so fast, guys.

997
01:00:31,374 --> 01:00:34,673
- Squints!
- You can't be a real team without...

998
01:00:34,744 --> 01:00:36,803
- Uniforms!
- Whoa!

999
01:00:36,880 --> 01:00:39,348
Squints, they look perfect!

1000
01:00:39,416 --> 01:00:41,680
- Far out.
- Just like you.

1001
01:00:41,751 --> 01:00:43,514
- Here you go, kid.
- All right.

1002
01:00:43,586 --> 01:00:46,180
- Come on, guys, pick a number.
- Whoa.

1003
01:00:46,256 --> 01:00:50,192
- I've got seven!
- I've got first dibs on 12!

1004
01:00:50,393 --> 01:00:53,021
% % [Patriotic]

1005
01:00:56,266 --> 01:01:01,363
Welcome one and all to the Valley
Little League Baseball Tournament.

1006
01:01:01,438 --> 01:01:04,566
Yes, where all teams are invited...

1007
01:01:04,641 --> 01:01:08,304
but only one team gets to take home
this here trophy.

1008
01:01:08,378 --> 01:01:10,972
So let's get to it. Play ball!

1009
01:01:11,047 --> 01:01:12,981
[All Shouting]

1010
01:01:13,049 --> 01:01:15,984
- <i>% % [Rock]</i>
- Okay, guys.

1011
01:01:16,052 --> 01:01:19,488
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

1012
01:01:24,594 --> 01:01:28,189
Come on, guys. Get back to the dugout.
Come on.

1013
01:01:28,264 --> 01:01:32,758
<i>[Two Ton]</i>
<i>Strike him out, Timber.</i>

1014
01:01:32,836 --> 01:01:35,168
<i>[Man] Out!</i>

1015
01:01:35,238 --> 01:01:37,866
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Come on, Ryan. Get it!</i>

1016
01:01:37,941 --> 01:01:40,102
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Out!</i>

1017
01:01:40,176 --> 01:01:43,612
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

1018
01:01:47,183 --> 01:01:49,845
- Come on, Tommy!
- [Cheering]

1019
01:02:01,631 --> 01:02:04,293
<i>Yeah, Tommy!</i>

1020
01:02:06,603 --> 01:02:09,629
- Hey, that Santorelli kid, he ain't bad.
- Ain't bad?

1021
01:02:09,706 --> 01:02:13,267
The kid's the best thing to happen to the sandlot
since the day Benny conquered the beast.

1022
01:02:20,350 --> 01:02:24,286
<i>[Two Ton]</i>
<i>Make way for Two Ton.</i>

1023
01:02:24,354 --> 01:02:26,549
- Play ball!
- <i>[Woman] All right, Two Ton.</i>

1024
01:02:26,623 --> 01:02:30,252
<i>All right, Two Ton,</i>
<i>bring Tommy home.</i>

1025
01:02:30,326 --> 01:02:32,453
Let's go.

1026
01:02:33,730 --> 01:02:36,096
<i>Strike one!</i>

1027
01:02:45,475 --> 01:02:48,410
<i>[Timber] Keep going! Keep going!</i>
<i>Keep going, keep going!</i>

1028
01:02:48,478 --> 01:02:51,003
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

1029
01:02:55,185 --> 01:02:58,643
- Down! Down!
- He's safe!

1030
01:03:02,425 --> 01:03:06,156
- <i>Nice!</i>
- Ohh!

1031
01:03:17,774 --> 01:03:21,141
- Out!
- [Cheering]

1032
01:03:25,381 --> 01:03:27,508
- That's two in a row.
- Two to go.

1033
01:03:27,584 --> 01:03:30,644
We keep this up, we'll be playing
Needman's team in the championships.

1034
01:03:30,720 --> 01:03:32,847
With Tommy, I think
we might actually have a shot.

1035
01:03:32,922 --> 01:03:36,119
All right, fellows, good game.
Get in the dugout, batting order. Let's go.

1036
01:03:36,192 --> 01:03:39,025
Hey, Chop. Any inside word
on the city council vote?

1037
01:03:39,095 --> 01:03:42,724
Oh, yeah. Split straight down
the center every time.

1038
01:03:42,799 --> 01:03:44,994
What's it going to take to
get this thing behind us?

1039
01:03:45,068 --> 01:03:47,832
<i>% % [Continues]</i>

1040
01:04:05,822 --> 01:04:09,724
Mom! Mom! We won! We won.

1041
01:04:09,792 --> 01:04:11,987
<i>That's great, sweetheart.</i>

1042
01:04:12,061 --> 01:04:14,894
- <i>% % [Ends]</i>
- Honey, we have a visitor.

1043
01:04:14,964 --> 01:04:19,367
Mr. Needman came by and has something
very important to talk to you about.

1044
01:04:19,435 --> 01:04:24,668
I saw you play today. You've got a lot
of potential, if you're on the right team.

1045
01:04:25,808 --> 01:04:27,833
Needman.

1046
01:04:27,911 --> 01:04:31,711
<i>[Projector Whirring]</i>

1047
01:04:31,781 --> 01:04:34,773
<i>[Crowd Cheering]</i>

1048
01:04:34,851 --> 01:04:37,285
Of course.

1049
01:04:42,125 --> 01:04:44,184
<i>[Gavel Raps]</i>

1050
01:04:44,260 --> 01:04:47,593
Mr. Chairman,
have we come to a decision?

1051
01:04:47,664 --> 01:04:52,294
Sadly, we have not. The vote
was a dead tie every time we took it...

1052
01:04:52,368 --> 01:04:54,427
<i>which brings us</i>
<i>to a crossroads, I'm afraid.</i>

1053
01:04:54,504 --> 01:04:56,870
We will have to push this back
until next quarter.

1054
01:04:56,940 --> 01:04:59,408
What?
You can't do that!

1055
01:04:59,475 --> 01:05:03,138
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait a minute now.
We have to act on this now.

1056
01:05:03,213 --> 01:05:06,239
- <i>[Man] Yes.</i>
- I'm open to suggestions.

1057
01:05:06,316 --> 01:05:10,082
- Why don't you just give it
to my dad? He deserves it.
- Shut up.

1058
01:05:10,153 --> 01:05:12,383
Well, Mr. Chairman, if I may...

1059
01:05:12,455 --> 01:05:17,154
I think I have a solution that would be
the fairest way to settle this matter.

1060
01:05:17,227 --> 01:05:20,128
I'd love to hear it.

1061
01:05:20,196 --> 01:05:23,063
Well, I'm not one
to believe in miracles...

1062
01:05:23,132 --> 01:05:26,329
but it appears
Mr. Palledorous's Sandlot team...

1063
01:05:26,402 --> 01:05:31,465
<i>is playing my team in the All-Valley</i>
<i>Championship Baseball Tournament.</i>

1064
01:05:31,541 --> 01:05:34,442
Yes, we're all proud
of our sandlot boys.

1065
01:05:34,510 --> 01:05:36,603
I propose a challenge.

1066
01:05:36,679 --> 01:05:42,515
If my team wins, we get to build
and develop on the sandlot.

1067
01:05:42,585 --> 01:05:47,113
<i>Mr. Palledorous's team wins,</i>
<i>the sandlot stays.</i>

1068
01:05:47,190 --> 01:05:51,923
- I'm in for that. Hear, hear!
- <i>[Chattering]</i>

1069
01:05:53,663 --> 01:05:56,029
<i>All right.</i>

1070
01:05:56,099 --> 01:05:59,330
We have no objections, if Mr. Palledorous
will honor the challenge.

1071
01:05:59,402 --> 01:06:02,303
Do it, Squints.
The kids are playing great ball...

1072
01:06:02,372 --> 01:06:05,808
and with Santorelli in center field,
we can't be beat.

1073
01:06:05,875 --> 01:06:09,675
[Chattering]

1074
01:06:09,746 --> 01:06:13,842
All right, Mr. Chairman.
We accept the challenge.

1075
01:06:13,916 --> 01:06:15,975
<i>[Cheering]</i>

1076
01:06:16,052 --> 01:06:18,111
On one condition.

1077
01:06:18,187 --> 01:06:23,022
The game for the sandlot
is played on the sandlot.

1078
01:06:23,092 --> 01:06:25,458
- <i>[Cheering]</i>
- Done!

1079
01:06:28,364 --> 01:06:31,162
<i>[Tommy]</i>
<i>So, you see, guys? I have no choice.</i>

1080
01:06:31,234 --> 01:06:33,225
<i>I have to play for Needman.</i>

1081
01:06:33,303 --> 01:06:36,170
<i>I made the over-the-wall catch</i>
<i>in the bottom of the ninth...</i>

1082
01:06:36,239 --> 01:06:38,503
<i>to win the All-City Championship.</i>

1083
01:06:38,574 --> 01:06:44,035
And Needman had the St. Agnus coach come
to that game, and he saw the whole thing.

1084
01:06:44,113 --> 01:06:48,573
So, you see, it was because of that catch
I got into St. Agnus Prep.

1085
01:06:48,651 --> 01:06:52,985
Because of my years in St. Agnus,
I got scouted and drafted in the first place.

1086
01:06:53,056 --> 01:06:55,547
So I have to do it.

1087
01:06:55,625 --> 01:06:57,991
<i>I've got no other choice here.</i>

1088
01:06:58,061 --> 01:07:00,256
Plus my mom thinks
it's the best thing for me.

1089
01:07:01,898 --> 01:07:05,664
I can't risk my whole future
for the sandlot, can I?

1090
01:07:09,772 --> 01:07:12,502
Maybe you're the one who
shouldn't speak for a while.

1091
01:07:12,575 --> 01:07:14,941
You can talk?

1092
01:07:19,349 --> 01:07:22,182
<i>Hey, wait! Ryan!</i>

1093
01:07:22,251 --> 01:07:24,583
<i>Hold on a sec!</i>

1094
01:07:24,654 --> 01:07:27,953
Ryan.
Hey, why did you do that?

1095
01:07:29,692 --> 01:07:33,184
You play with us, teach us all
this great stuff about baseball...

1096
01:07:33,262 --> 01:07:35,253
being a team,
playing together.

1097
01:07:35,331 --> 01:07:37,891
- Now you're going to up and leave us?
- But I have to.

1098
01:07:37,967 --> 01:07:40,527
You don't have to do nothing.
You're a crock, man.

1099
01:07:40,603 --> 01:07:44,300
We looked up to you. You made us
feel for the game, and it showed.

1100
01:07:44,374 --> 01:07:48,367
- I thought we were showing you something too.
- Yeah? What's that?

1101
01:07:48,444 --> 01:07:51,140
Friendship, dummy.

1102
01:07:57,487 --> 01:08:00,388
- <i>[Baseball Bat Cracks]</i>
- <i>Yeah, get it, Tommy.</i>

1103
01:08:00,456 --> 01:08:04,586
- <i>Come on, Tommy!</i>
- <i>Come on! Come on!</i>

1104
01:08:04,660 --> 01:08:08,061
- <i>[Boy] What? Come on.</i>
- <i>[Boy #2] What was that?</i>

1105
01:08:11,334 --> 01:08:15,430
Look, I don't know how
you do things over there in Loserville...

1106
01:08:15,505 --> 01:08:18,406
but here we have a way
of doing things.

1107
01:08:18,474 --> 01:08:21,841
We hit the cutoff man.
Do you understand me?

1108
01:08:21,911 --> 01:08:26,109
Just let me do what I have to do.
Leave me alone, E.J.

1109
01:08:26,182 --> 01:08:29,242
- Something wrong, Santorelli?
- I'm here, aren't I?

1110
01:08:29,318 --> 01:08:31,786
Yeah, well, at the big
championship game...

1111
01:08:31,854 --> 01:08:34,448
I'm going to need you more
than just here, you understand?

1112
01:08:34,524 --> 01:08:37,118
A lot of people counting on you, boy.

1113
01:08:37,193 --> 01:08:40,026
- I'll be fine.
- For your sake, I hope so.

1114
01:08:40,096 --> 01:08:42,530
And the rest of you guys,
you've all got to work harder.

1115
01:08:42,598 --> 01:08:45,999
I bet that other team is busting their butts
trying to get ready for this game!

1116
01:08:46,068 --> 01:08:51,165
- <i>[D.P.] Oh! No way!</i>
- Seven jawbreakers, ladies and gentlemen!

1117
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:54,300
- Whoa, good job, Two Ton.
- <i>He's gonna pop, guys!</i>

1118
01:08:54,377 --> 01:08:57,938
[All Screaming]

1119
01:08:58,014 --> 01:09:02,178
You've got to lay off the jawbreakers, man.
You're gonna put somebody's eye out.

1120
01:09:02,251 --> 01:09:04,685
Hey, guys, shouldn't we be
practicing for the big game?

1121
01:09:04,754 --> 01:09:07,484
Give me some more.
I'm going for eight.

1122
01:09:07,557 --> 01:09:10,355
- <i>[D.P.] Beat your own record.</i>
- Put them in.

1123
01:09:10,426 --> 01:09:12,155
- Go! Go!
- <i>Put more.</i>

1124
01:09:17,467 --> 01:09:19,992
- Hey, sorry I'm late, buddy.
- Oh, Benny.

1125
01:09:20,069 --> 01:09:23,470
You didn't have to come help. I'm sure
you must have more important things to do.

1126
01:09:23,539 --> 01:09:25,564
Come on.
What's more important than this?

1127
01:09:25,641 --> 01:09:28,804
Looks good.
The old gang would be proud.

1128
01:09:28,878 --> 01:09:31,403
[Squints] hey, did you hear ham
is wrestling at the State Fair next month?

1129
01:09:31,481 --> 01:09:34,075
The old hambino is still at it, huh?

1130
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:39,417
- How's your knee?
- Ah, Doc says I'll probably be
out for the rest of the season.

1131
01:09:39,489 --> 01:09:42,219
- I'm sorry, Benny.
- Hey, don't be. I'll be all right.

1132
01:09:42,291 --> 01:09:45,317
Nothing like it though, huh?

1133
01:09:45,394 --> 01:09:48,488
Coming out to the old ball field,
spending the summer with your friends...

1134
01:09:48,564 --> 01:09:51,863
- playing the sport you love.
- Yeah.

1135
01:09:51,934 --> 01:09:54,266
Playing in the majors
must be really great, huh?

1136
01:09:54,337 --> 01:09:57,238
I was talking about you guys.

1137
01:10:01,177 --> 01:10:04,112
<i>[Ryan's Voice]</i>
<i>Friendship, dummy.</i>

1138
01:10:07,783 --> 01:10:09,717
- So how's Wendy?
- Great.

1139
01:10:09,785 --> 01:10:13,721
- <i>[Benny] Yeah? How many kids you got now?</i>
- Oh, four.

1140
01:10:13,789 --> 01:10:17,190
- <i>Bet they're keeping you busy.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

1141
01:10:17,260 --> 01:10:19,319
[Sighs]

1142
01:10:35,945 --> 01:10:38,379
[Sighs]

1143
01:10:43,886 --> 01:10:45,979
Hey.

1144
01:10:47,957 --> 01:10:50,448
Why aren't you at the game?

1145
01:10:50,526 --> 01:10:53,154
I don't know if I should go.

1146
01:10:53,229 --> 01:10:55,789
Why not?

1147
01:10:55,865 --> 01:10:58,356
Because I need to be here with you.

1148
01:11:01,370 --> 01:11:03,463
Honey, come here.

1149
01:11:12,882 --> 01:11:17,512
I'm so grateful to have
such a wonderful son.

1150
01:11:19,488 --> 01:11:22,321
Now you go play
the game you love.

1151
01:11:22,391 --> 01:11:24,951
<i>I'll be here when you get back.</i>

1152
01:11:25,027 --> 01:11:29,430
Good things happen
to good people, Tommy.

1153
01:11:33,536 --> 01:11:36,004
I'll come home as soon
as the game's over.

1154
01:11:36,072 --> 01:11:38,506
I promise.

1155
01:11:42,511 --> 01:11:45,105
I love you, Mom.

1156
01:11:50,186 --> 01:11:53,155
- [Man] I know. Exactly. That's the problem.
- Sit down. I saved a spot.

1157
01:11:53,222 --> 01:11:56,214
<i>This place is a disaster.</i>

1158
01:11:57,693 --> 01:12:00,560
- This place is a gift.
- <i>What do you mean?</i>

1159
01:12:00,630 --> 01:12:05,294
I helped my dad measure this dump. We cream
the ball, even you could hit a home run.

1160
01:12:05,368 --> 01:12:08,132
- <i>[Needman] Let's go, guys.</i>
<i>Go on. Get in here. Hustle up!</i>
- Yeah!

1161
01:12:09,605 --> 01:12:11,903
- So what are we going to do today?
- [All] Win!

1162
01:12:11,974 --> 01:12:16,035
That's right, and I'm gonna bulldoze
this place first thing in the morning.

1163
01:12:16,112 --> 01:12:18,307
Hey, Bill!

1164
01:12:20,716 --> 01:12:22,843
- How are you doing?
- Better than a doubleheader on Sundays.

1165
01:12:22,918 --> 01:12:25,887
- What do you got for me today?
- I got something good for you today.

1166
01:12:25,955 --> 01:12:30,085
- I hope it's better than that hair.
- Yeah. Yeah. E. J!

1167
01:12:30,159 --> 01:12:32,559
- Come on over here. You remember E.J.
- Oh, absolutely.

1168
01:12:32,628 --> 01:12:35,722
- E.J., how are you doing?
- How could I forget? Nice to meet you.

1169
01:12:35,798 --> 01:12:38,494
Nice to meet you too. But how about that
Santorelli kid I've been hearing about?

1170
01:12:38,567 --> 01:12:42,162
- They tell me a lot about him.
I want to see him.
- Oh, yeah, yeah. Uh, Tommy.

1171
01:12:42,238 --> 01:12:45,765
- Come on over here.
I've got somebody for you to meet.
- Hey, Tommy. How are you doing?

1172
01:12:45,841 --> 01:12:49,174
I've heard a lot about you. I've come to watch
you play. I want to see what you can do.

1173
01:12:49,245 --> 01:12:52,408
- Yeah. E.J. Here, he's been...
- I've been practicing.

1174
01:12:52,481 --> 01:12:55,348
- I've heard a lot about you too.
- Okay, well, I'm going to go warm up.

1175
01:12:55,418 --> 01:12:57,852
- All right, Tommy. Nice to meet you.
- Nice seeing you.

1176
01:12:57,920 --> 01:13:01,754
- I'm gonna go warm up.
You won't be disappointed.
- All right. Yeah, l... I hope not.

1177
01:13:01,824 --> 01:13:03,883
No. E.J., he's...
he's been improving, yeah.

1178
01:13:03,959 --> 01:13:07,053
- Yeah, well, he has great coaching.
- Yeah, yeah, that's right, yeah.

1179
01:13:07,129 --> 01:13:09,689
Welcome to the Valley Little League
Tournament championship game.

1180
01:13:09,765 --> 01:13:13,565
Ladies and gentlemen, will you please
rise for our national anthem.

1181
01:13:13,636 --> 01:13:17,629
<i>% % [Patriotic]</i>

1182
01:13:44,467 --> 01:13:46,492
- <i>% % [Ends]</i>
- Let's do this!

1183
01:13:46,569 --> 01:13:50,437
- Dork.
- <i>[Boy] All right. Let's go.</i>
<i>Let's cream these losers.</i>

1184
01:13:56,512 --> 01:14:00,278
[Whispering]
Good luck.

1185
01:14:00,349 --> 01:14:02,010
They'll be sorry
they were ever born.

1186
01:14:02,084 --> 01:14:04,314
I still can't believe
he'd play for Needman!

1187
01:14:04,386 --> 01:14:07,651
- I knew he was a traitor all along.
- So duplicitous.

1188
01:14:07,723 --> 01:14:13,127
Man, we are so dead. Not only did we
lose Tommy, but we're minus a player.

1189
01:14:13,195 --> 01:14:15,595
- All right, guys, listen up...
- I've got something to say.

1190
01:14:15,664 --> 01:14:18,360
- What?
- Did Ryan just speak?

1191
01:14:18,434 --> 01:14:21,528
<i>I've been around you guys</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

1192
01:14:21,604 --> 01:14:26,098
One thing I know is that Benny's right.
You guys love baseball.

1193
01:14:26,175 --> 01:14:30,441
You eat, drink and sleep baseball,
but nothing compares to playing it.

1194
01:14:30,513 --> 01:14:34,005
If we give up now, well, you can say
good-bye to the sandlot forever.

1195
01:14:34,083 --> 01:14:36,643
- But you don't...
- Zip it, tubby!

1196
01:14:36,719 --> 01:14:38,846
It's my turn to talk.

1197
01:14:38,921 --> 01:14:42,186
<i>Tommy taught us a lot</i>
<i>about baseball skills.</i>

1198
01:14:42,258 --> 01:14:46,024
Instead of being mad at him, let's show him
exactly what he failed to learn from us...

1199
01:14:46,095 --> 01:14:48,757
<i>how to play the game we love.</i>

1200
01:14:52,268 --> 01:14:56,170
I don't know about you guys, but I don't want
to lose this field to a bunch of butt-faces.

1201
01:14:56,238 --> 01:14:59,901
- The mouth on that kid.
- <i>So what are we gonna do today, boys?</i>

1202
01:14:59,975 --> 01:15:03,376
- We're gonna win!
- <i>That's right.</i>

1203
01:15:10,219 --> 01:15:13,711
All right, guys.

1204
01:15:13,789 --> 01:15:16,883
What he said.
Everybody in.

1205
01:15:16,959 --> 01:15:21,862
- Yeah!
- [All] One, two, three! Sandlots!

1206
01:15:24,667 --> 01:15:28,501
- I need to talk to you, Needman.
- Hey, isn't that that Santorelli kid?

1207
01:15:28,571 --> 01:15:30,903
I thought he was on the Sandlot team.

1208
01:15:30,973 --> 01:15:35,034
It ain't over till the fat lady sings.

1209
01:15:35,110 --> 01:15:39,410
Oh. Oh, uh, sorry.
[Chuckles]

1210
01:15:39,481 --> 01:15:43,713
- Take your position, Santorelli.
You can tell me after the game.
- But I need to talk to you!

1211
01:15:43,786 --> 01:15:47,517
Yeah! Whoo!

1212
01:15:50,426 --> 01:15:53,918
Are you deaf, son?
Move it. Now!

1213
01:15:56,599 --> 01:15:59,625
- Santorelli!
- What is he doing?

1214
01:15:59,702 --> 01:16:02,227
Where are you going?
I told you your position.

1215
01:16:02,304 --> 01:16:08,265
Wait! What are you doing, boy?
Son, you do not want to do this.

1216
01:16:08,344 --> 01:16:10,642
- What do you want?
- I want to win.

1217
01:16:10,713 --> 01:16:12,578
Yeah, so do we.

1218
01:16:12,648 --> 01:16:16,049
- Get lost, Tommy.
- Yeah, vamoose. We don't need you.

1219
01:16:16,118 --> 01:16:18,746
Look, I made a mistake.

1220
01:16:18,821 --> 01:16:22,723
- <i>I'm sorry.</i>
- What are you saying?

1221
01:16:22,791 --> 01:16:28,229
I made a deal to play for Needman's team,
because I thought it was my destiny.

1222
01:16:28,297 --> 01:16:30,765
This isn't the part where
you go off about the Dodgers...

1223
01:16:30,833 --> 01:16:33,825
<i>the Hall of Fame and your</i>
<i>smoking-hot girlfriends, is it?</i>

1224
01:16:33,903 --> 01:16:39,307
No. This is the part where I throw
that all away to do what's right.

1225
01:16:39,375 --> 01:16:42,742
Play ball with my friends.

1226
01:16:42,811 --> 01:16:45,336
- What did I say?
- That is, if you'll have me.

1227
01:16:49,184 --> 01:16:52,847
Look, I would rather lose
a game with my real team...

1228
01:16:52,922 --> 01:16:55,686
than win one
for all the wrong reasons.

1229
01:16:55,758 --> 01:16:57,749
You made a bad mistake.

1230
01:17:00,262 --> 01:17:03,026
We're not gonna lose.

1231
01:17:04,700 --> 01:17:07,965
<i>Take off that ridiculous uniform</i>
<i>and get ready to bat.</i>

1232
01:17:08,037 --> 01:17:10,369
Thanks, Tommy.

1233
01:17:12,074 --> 01:17:16,511
Son, you had me going there.
[Chuckles]

1234
01:17:16,578 --> 01:17:20,378
What are you doing? Now, that is not
the right decision to make there, boy.

1235
01:17:20,449 --> 01:17:23,612
Hey, Earl.

1236
01:17:23,686 --> 01:17:25,779
I won't be needing this anymore.

1237
01:17:25,854 --> 01:17:28,721
- <i>[Man] Whoa!</i>
- <i>[Cheering]</i>

1238
01:17:28,791 --> 01:17:32,056
Hey, good thing
I didn't throw this away.

1239
01:17:32,127 --> 01:17:34,357
- Great to have you back, Tommy.
- [All] Yeah!

1240
01:17:34,430 --> 01:17:37,456
Son, you can kiss St. Agnus good-bye.

1241
01:17:37,533 --> 01:17:40,661
Yeah, and that's not the half of it.

1242
01:17:40,736 --> 01:17:43,705
- We're gonna play ball or what?
- <i>[All] Yeah!</i>

1243
01:17:43,772 --> 01:17:46,036
Let's play ball.

1244
01:17:47,443 --> 01:17:50,537
All right.
Let's go!

1245
01:17:50,612 --> 01:17:53,706
<i>[Wok]</i>
<i>Nice hit, Tommy.</i>

1246
01:17:53,782 --> 01:17:57,912
<i>% % [Man Singing Country]</i>

1247
01:18:01,123 --> 01:18:04,581
- <i>% % [Continues]</i>
- Oh, get under it! Get under it!

1248
01:18:04,660 --> 01:18:07,754
[Clanking]

1249
01:18:07,830 --> 01:18:10,390
Yeah, I got it!

1250
01:18:13,802 --> 01:18:17,829
This way! No, that way! No...

1251
01:18:17,906 --> 01:18:20,067
- What are you doing?
- He's out of there!

1252
01:18:29,985 --> 01:18:31,885
Safe!

1253
01:18:35,758 --> 01:18:37,521
Out!

1254
01:18:43,699 --> 01:18:45,997
Come on, Sandlots!

1255
01:18:50,005 --> 01:18:51,939
Yeah! Go! Go!

1256
01:18:55,811 --> 01:18:58,109
You're out!

1257
01:18:58,180 --> 01:19:00,307
Whoo! You can do it!

1258
01:19:28,577 --> 01:19:31,512
- Safe!
- Let's go, boys!

1259
01:19:37,920 --> 01:19:40,286
- Safe!
- Come on, Two Ton!

1260
01:19:49,565 --> 01:19:51,999
- Are you okay?
- Man down! Man down!

1261
01:19:52,067 --> 01:19:54,092
Man out.

1262
01:20:04,146 --> 01:20:07,206
- <i>% % [Ends]</i>
- Out!

1263
01:20:19,261 --> 01:20:23,425
<i>[Timber] Come on, Tommy!</i>
<i>Send it to the North Pole.</i>

1264
01:20:24,800 --> 01:20:27,894
<i>[Boy] Hit a homer, Tommy!</i>
<i>Got a man on!</i>

1265
01:20:27,970 --> 01:20:30,063
Walk him, son.

1266
01:20:31,907 --> 01:20:35,468
- But, Dad...
- You do what I say.

1267
01:20:35,544 --> 01:20:39,742
Hey, Needman. You really going to put
the tying run in scoring position?

1268
01:20:39,815 --> 01:20:43,911
Hey, Rodriguez, you coach your team
and I'll coach mine, all right?

1269
01:20:43,986 --> 01:20:47,478
But, Dad... I mean, Coach,
I can take this guy.

1270
01:20:47,556 --> 01:20:49,581
Time.

1271
01:20:54,329 --> 01:20:57,264
- I can get him out.
- Son, it is too risky.

1272
01:20:57,332 --> 01:21:01,769
<i>Look, I got him down.</i>
<i>This punk can't hit the outside pitch.</i>

1273
01:21:01,837 --> 01:21:05,568
- I promise you he's all mine.
- No, E.J.

1274
01:21:05,641 --> 01:21:08,906
You always said a Needman
never backs down from a fight.

1275
01:21:08,977 --> 01:21:12,504
Yeah?
Well, I'm not backing down.

1276
01:21:14,183 --> 01:21:17,380
All right,
but if you're wrong...

1277
01:21:17,452 --> 01:21:21,286
your new 10-speed bike is going
in the wood chipper, you understand me?

1278
01:21:21,356 --> 01:21:23,290
Two words: Wood chipper.

1279
01:21:23,358 --> 01:21:25,986
<i>Play ball!</i>

1280
01:21:31,767 --> 01:21:34,395
Strike one!

1281
01:21:34,469 --> 01:21:37,404
Good pitch, pitcher.

1282
01:21:46,648 --> 01:21:50,482
<i>Strike two!</i>

1283
01:21:56,959 --> 01:22:00,827
- Come on, boy.
- Don't worry about it, Tommy.

1284
01:22:18,814 --> 01:22:22,250
- [Cheering]
- <i>[Man] Foul ball!</i>

1285
01:22:22,317 --> 01:22:25,252
[Groaning]

1286
01:22:25,320 --> 01:22:27,288
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Nice try, Tommy.</i>

1287
01:22:27,356 --> 01:22:29,347
Come on!
Put it through his kitchen!

1288
01:22:29,424 --> 01:22:33,451
Go, Tommy!

1289
01:22:33,528 --> 01:22:37,020
Hey, Santa, is that
the North Pole out there?

1290
01:22:39,601 --> 01:22:42,365
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Go, Santa!</i>

1291
01:22:48,243 --> 01:22:51,007
That's it, E.J.
You got him just where you want him.

1292
01:22:53,115 --> 01:22:57,677
[Scoffs]
You're out of here.

1293
01:22:57,753 --> 01:23:00,347
So is this next pitch.

1294
01:23:15,070 --> 01:23:19,166
- <i>Run! Run! Run!</i>
- <i>[Glass Shattering]</i>

1295
01:23:19,241 --> 01:23:21,903
[Cheering]

1296
01:23:21,977 --> 01:23:24,411
I loved that 10-speed!

1297
01:23:30,652 --> 01:23:35,180
- Three more outs...
- And the sandlot is saved.

1298
01:23:37,159 --> 01:23:41,892
<i>[Tommy] This is it, guys.</i>
<i>Three outs and the sandlot's ours forever.</i>

1299
01:23:41,963 --> 01:23:47,833
One more thing. We're gonna use this ball
this inning for luck, remember?

1300
01:23:47,903 --> 01:23:51,100
Okay. On three!

1301
01:23:51,173 --> 01:23:56,509
- [Together] One, two, three! Sandlots!
- Let's go!

1302
01:24:02,117 --> 01:24:05,416
Hey, batter.
You've got some... 'sup on your shoe.

1303
01:24:05,487 --> 01:24:09,389
- What's 'sup?
- Oh, l-I don't know. What's up with you?

1304
01:24:09,458 --> 01:24:13,519
- Strike three!
- L... I wasn't ready!

1305
01:24:13,595 --> 01:24:15,426
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Out!</i>

1306
01:24:15,497 --> 01:24:17,931
What?
I was gonna hit a homer!

1307
01:24:17,999 --> 01:24:21,560
- Get out of my way.
- You were supposed to walk.

1308
01:24:21,636 --> 01:24:23,968
I swing if I want to swing.

1309
01:24:26,141 --> 01:24:30,771
- [Exhales]
- <i>[Boy] All right, guys, let's go.</i>

1310
01:24:32,681 --> 01:24:37,243
- Keep your eye on the ball.
- <i>[Wok] Strike him out!</i>

1311
01:24:39,221 --> 01:24:43,157
- You're out!
- Nice!

1312
01:24:43,225 --> 01:24:47,321
Sucker. Two out, guys!

1313
01:24:47,396 --> 01:24:49,296
<i>Two out.</i>

1314
01:24:49,364 --> 01:24:52,390
Okay, one more out
and the sandlot lives.

1315
01:24:52,467 --> 01:24:56,062
- <i>[Boy] One more out!</i>
- Get 'em, E.J.

1316
01:24:56,138 --> 01:24:57,662
<i>You're not number one for nothing.</i>

1317
01:24:57,739 --> 01:25:00,333
- <i>Like father, like son.</i>
- Out of my way, dork.

1318
01:25:02,377 --> 01:25:05,312
Hey, what's that I smell?
[Sniffs]

1319
01:25:05,380 --> 01:25:08,645
- <i>Come on, EJ!</i>
- Oh, it's just Needman!

1320
01:25:08,717 --> 01:25:11,982
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Don't strike out!</i>

1321
01:25:12,053 --> 01:25:14,317
All right, Timber.
It's okay, Timber.

1322
01:25:17,993 --> 01:25:21,986
<i>[Wok]</i>
<i>Come on, Timber.</i>

1323
01:25:28,336 --> 01:25:30,668
Time!

1324
01:25:33,575 --> 01:25:36,305
- <i>[Crowd Groans]</i>
- <i>[Woman] Come on!</i>

1325
01:25:40,081 --> 01:25:42,948
He's just scared, Timber.
Give him the heat.

1326
01:25:45,120 --> 01:25:48,385
Let's go, Timber!
Time's a-wasting.

1327
01:25:59,468 --> 01:26:02,062
- Just throw it right in there.
Bring him the heat.
- Show him some heat!

1328
01:26:28,196 --> 01:26:30,221
[No Audible Dialogue]

1329
01:26:43,245 --> 01:26:45,270
[No Audible Dialogue]

1330
01:26:56,358 --> 01:27:00,260
[Screaming]

1331
01:27:04,466 --> 01:27:06,957
Yeah!
That's my boy! Yeah!

1332
01:27:15,644 --> 01:27:18,044
- <i>[Man] Yeah!</i>
- [Cheering]

1333
01:27:18,113 --> 01:27:20,604
- Batter out!
- What?

1334
01:27:20,682 --> 01:27:22,775
- Look! What are you talking about?
- He caught the ball.

1335
01:27:22,851 --> 01:27:25,319
<i>It touched no ground.</i>
<i>He's out!</i>

1336
01:27:30,959 --> 01:27:33,792
- Yeah, guys!
- Tommy!

1337
01:27:33,862 --> 01:27:35,955
Nice catch, kid.

1338
01:27:52,213 --> 01:27:54,306
Geez!

1339
01:27:56,351 --> 01:28:00,344
We're, uh, not going to have
a situation here, are we, Earl?

1340
01:28:00,422 --> 01:28:04,153
'Cause, uh,
we don't want a situation.

1341
01:28:04,225 --> 01:28:06,989
Yeah, Sandlot!

1342
01:28:07,062 --> 01:28:09,860
- Whoo!
- Yeah, all right!

1343
01:28:09,931 --> 01:28:12,695
- [Grunts]
- You were right about that Santorelli kid.

1344
01:28:12,767 --> 01:28:14,792
He's gonna be an all-star.

1345
01:28:14,869 --> 01:28:17,770
What about that deal with my son?
He's quite the athlete, huh?

1346
01:28:17,839 --> 01:28:22,276
I'm not looking for athletes. I'm looking
for ballplayers, and I just found one.

1347
01:28:22,344 --> 01:28:27,179
- [Cheering]
- Guys! Guys! Guys!

1348
01:28:27,248 --> 01:28:29,273
It's been the best game of my life.

1349
01:28:29,351 --> 01:28:31,785
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Obviously.

1350
01:28:31,853 --> 01:28:35,186
- But I've got to go.
- What? We just won the big game.

1351
01:28:35,256 --> 01:28:37,816
At least stick around for the fireworks
and the trophy ceremony.

1352
01:28:37,892 --> 01:28:41,851
- [All] Yeah!
- I'm sorry, guys. I'm sorry.

1353
01:28:41,930 --> 01:28:44,228
I gotta go see my mom.

1354
01:29:01,216 --> 01:29:03,309
<i>[Squints]</i>
<i>Hey, guys.</i>

1355
01:29:03,385 --> 01:29:06,081
- I think Benny's got something to say to you.
- Oh, yeah.

1356
01:29:06,154 --> 01:29:09,180
Uh, I think there's something over there
that belongs to you guys!

1357
01:29:09,257 --> 01:29:11,885
[All]
Yeah!

1358
01:29:11,960 --> 01:29:15,088
Wow! We did it!

1359
01:29:18,933 --> 01:29:22,232
The sandlot's been saved!

1360
01:29:35,850 --> 01:29:40,048
You always knew
how to make me proud.

1361
01:29:40,121 --> 01:29:42,055
[Labored Breathing]

1362
01:29:42,123 --> 01:29:44,216
- <i>[Tap On Glass]</i>
- <i>[Ryan] Tommy.</i>

1363
01:29:50,598 --> 01:29:54,864
- Tommy, you forgot this.
- <i>What are you doing here?</i>

1364
01:29:54,936 --> 01:29:57,564
You're going to miss the trophy
ceremony and the fireworks!

1365
01:29:57,639 --> 01:30:01,097
- <i>[Fireworks Exploding]</i>
- Who cares? This belongs to you.

1366
01:30:14,355 --> 01:30:17,449
- I think he's waking up, Doctor.
- <i>[Man] Welcome back.</i>

1367
01:30:17,525 --> 01:30:20,289
What happened?
Where am I?

1368
01:30:20,361 --> 01:30:22,420
You're at Cedars-Sinai, Tommy.

1369
01:30:22,497 --> 01:30:24,795
When I, uh, heard you took
a pitch to the head in practice...

1370
01:30:24,866 --> 01:30:27,733
<i>I raced over here</i>
<i>to check in on you.</i>

1371
01:30:27,802 --> 01:30:30,566
- <i>Q?</i>
- No one's called me that in years.

1372
01:30:32,574 --> 01:30:35,771
Oh, I had...
I had the strangest dream.

1373
01:30:35,844 --> 01:30:40,008
- Hey, he's awake, everyone.
- Well, who's here?

1374
01:30:40,081 --> 01:30:42,811
Are you kidding?
More like who isn't.

1375
01:30:42,884 --> 01:30:46,411
- Hey, there's my boy!
- <i>Benny, what are you doing here?</i>

1376
01:30:46,488 --> 01:30:50,185
- What? A manager can't visit his favorite player?
- His favorite what?

1377
01:30:50,258 --> 01:30:55,355
Yeah, you know, the guys have been here
almost every day. You know, just checking in.

1378
01:30:55,430 --> 01:30:58,763
- They were really worried about their captain.
- Captain?

1379
01:30:58,833 --> 01:31:02,030
- <i>How could you scare me like that, you silly man.</i>
- Judy?

1380
01:31:02,103 --> 01:31:04,867
I'm glad to see
you recognize your own wife.

1381
01:31:09,177 --> 01:31:15,309
L... I missed you so much.
I'm sorry that I ever left you.

1382
01:31:15,383 --> 01:31:19,342
- What are you talking about?
- When I went to New York to play for the Yankees.

1383
01:31:19,420 --> 01:31:22,514
<i>[Benny] Hey, pal. You never</i>
<i>played for the Yankees.</i>

1384
01:31:22,590 --> 01:31:25,115
You've been a Dodger
your whole career.

1385
01:31:25,193 --> 01:31:29,994
<i>Hey, he may be a little groggy,</i>
<i>but don't worry, Judy. He'll be fine.</i>

1386
01:31:30,064 --> 01:31:34,160
Remember, honey? You chose
to stay with me in L.A.

1387
01:31:34,235 --> 01:31:37,568
- I did?
- Yeah. Yeah, you did.

1388
01:31:41,376 --> 01:31:44,038
Heather. Oliver.
Daddy's awake.

1389
01:31:44,112 --> 01:31:47,411
- We-We have ki...
- <i>Daddy! Daddy, you're awake!</i>

1390
01:31:47,482 --> 01:31:50,246
Oh, we have kids.

1391
01:31:50,318 --> 01:31:54,550
- Hey. Hey, boy.
- Daddy, I was so worried about you.

1392
01:31:59,994 --> 01:32:03,987
Looks like this old ball still has
some luck in her yet, huh, buddy?

1393
01:32:04,065 --> 01:32:06,192
Ryan?

1394
01:32:06,267 --> 01:32:09,202
Do you realize how many calls
we get every day asking about you?

1395
01:32:09,270 --> 01:32:13,764
- Calls?
- Yeah. On my sports radio show.

1396
01:32:13,842 --> 01:32:16,003
Hey, some of the guys
want to come in and say hi.

1397
01:32:27,422 --> 01:32:30,619
<i>[Thinking: Boys' Voices]</i>
<i>All right, Tommy!</i>

1398
01:32:32,994 --> 01:32:37,761
It's just like you said, Mom.
Good things to good people.

1399
01:32:40,201 --> 01:32:45,639
<i>[Crowd Cheering]</i>

1400
01:32:47,542 --> 01:32:51,308
Tommy Santorelli...
14-time all-star...

1401
01:32:51,379 --> 01:32:55,213
three-time World Series champion,
M.V.P. Of two of them.

1402
01:32:55,283 --> 01:32:59,413
But, uh, that's not the only reason
he's going straight to Cooperstown.

1403
01:32:59,487 --> 01:33:04,982
Tommy could be the most loved player,
teammate and leader the game's ever seen.

1404
01:33:05,059 --> 01:33:07,994
<i>Having played his entire</i>
<i>career for the Dodgers...</i>

1405
01:33:08,062 --> 01:33:11,998
<i>Tommy turned down big money</i>
<i>offers from other teams over the years.</i>

1406
01:33:12,066 --> 01:33:16,628
<i>But the thing he treasures</i>
<i>most to this day is saving the sandlot.</i>

1407
01:33:16,704 --> 01:33:20,231
<i>[Tommy]</i>
<i>Forever.</i>

1408
01:36:29,004 --> 01:36:30,231
The end

